<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <title>Weather App API Documentation</title>
</head>

<body>

    {{>nav}}
    <div class="container-fluid">
        <div class="text-center py-4">
            <h2>Welcome to the Weather App API</h2>
            <p class="lead">API Documentation</p>
        </div>

        <div class="row justify-content-center align-items-center">
            <div class="col-8">
                <h4>Weather Data Endpoint</h4>
                <p>Use this endpoint to get weather data for a specific location.</p>
                <p><strong>Endpoint:</strong> /weather</p>
                <p><strong>Method:</strong> GET</p>
                <p><strong>Parameters:</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>address:</strong> The location for which you want to retrieve weather data.</li>
                </ul>
                <p><strong>Response:</strong> The API returns a JSON object containing the location and current weather information.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row justify-content-center align-items-center mt-4">
            <div class="col-8">
                <h4>Error Handling</h4>
                <p>The API may return an error if the provided location is not found or if there is an issue with the request. Error responses will include appropriate error messages and status codes.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row justify-content-center align-items-center mt-4">
            <div class="col-8">
                <h4>Example Usage</h4>
                <p>To retrieve weather data for New York City, make a GET request to the following endpoint: <code>/weather?address=New%20York%20City</code>.</p>
                <p>The API will respond with the current weather data for New York City in JSON format.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
    <script src="/js/app.js"></script>
</body>

</html>
